last_episode_to_air.name: See You Later, Alligator!
last_episode_to_air.overview: Bayou Chicken Farmers Deema and Goby discover an unusual egg on their farm one morning, and set off on a bayou river adventure to find the egg's mama.

name: Bubble Guppies
overview: The adventures of seven fish-tailed kids- Molly, Gil, Oona, Deema, Nonny, Goby, and Zooli!

episodes.name: Call a Clambulance!
episodes.overview: Oona's friend Avi broke a bone in his tail and has gone to see a doctor. The Bubble Guppies aren't too worried--after all, it's a doctor's job to make Avi feel better. Everybody say "Ahhhh!"

episodes.name: The Crayon Prix!
episodes.overview: Green means GO! The Bubble Guppies are racing their quick, colorful cars for the ultimate prize--a big box of crayons! Take the wheel and help the racers mix colors, make new shades, and speed across the finish line!

episodes.name: Bubble Puppy!
episodes.overview: Sit! Stay! Fetch! Gil wants to adopt a puppy! But the Bubble Guppies have to learn how to take care of a pet before he can bring the little guy home.

episodes.name: Build Me a Building!
episodes.overview: It's going to be the best doghouse EVER! But before Bubble Puppy can move into his new doggy digs the Bubble Guppies have to build it. So put on your hard hat and roll up your sleeves; construction is about to begin.

episodes.name: Ducks in a Row!
episodes.overview: Duck! Nonny meets a Marching Band with a Duck problem. The Duck is in the way and they can't play their instruments! But with a little whistle, and a little help from Mr. Grouper and the Bubble Guppies, Nonny learns how to lead the Marching Band--ducks or no ducks.

episodes.name: The Grumpfish Special!
episodes.overview: At the Bubble Guppies restaurant you'll get a picture on your pizza and a smile on your face, unless of course you're the Grumpfish. From waiting tables to cooking food, the Bubble Guppies prepare to serve their most difficult customer yet. But is there anything on the menu that can get the Grumpfish grinning?

episodes.name: The Moon Rocks!
episodes.overview: Have you ever seen the moon in the daytime? Have you ever noticed it kinda looks like a big pizza? The Guppies have! Blast off and leave your home planet behind--it's time to check out the solar system with the Bubble Guppies!

episodes.name: Who's Gonna Play the Big Bad Wolf?
episodes.overview: Set the stage and light the lights! The Bubble Guppies are learning about plays! They're going to see the all-starfish production of "The Three Little Pigs." But when one of the actors can't perform, it's up to Deema to put on the costume and take the stage. It's show time!

episodes.name: We Totally Rock!
episodes.overview: Are you ready to rock? The Bubble Guppies are taking the stage with their guitars, drums and keyboards. Get ready to crank it up to 10 and learn about everything rock and roll.

episodes.name: Fishketball!
episodes.overview: The Bubble Guppies explore different kinds of ball games as they get ready for their big game of Fishketball! Join Team Guppies to help them practice bouncing, throwing, catching and playing together as a team.

episodes.name: The Legend of Pinkfoot!
episodes.overview: The Bubble Guppies are going on a camping trip! Grab your flashlights and gather around the campfire to make s'mores and hear about the spooky legend of Pinkfoot!

episodes.name: Gup, Gup and Away!
episodes.overview: Pack a suitcase and hurry to the airport! Help the Bubble Guppies fly an airplane through the sky and over the clouds-just be sure to keep an eye out for airplane pirates!

episodes.name: The Spring Chicken Is Coming!
episodes.overview: The Guppies have to plant a flower for the Spring Chicken.

episodes.name: Boy Meets Squirrel!
episodes.overview: A squirrel named Doug gives Nonny an acorn, making Nonny wonder if it can become an acorn tree. But the Guppies have to learn about trees (and recycling) first!

episodes.name: Have a Cow!
episodes.overview: A mother cow named Butterscotch is about to give birth to a new baby. Note: This is the Mother's Day special. Mr. Grouper sing the pop song instead of Molly or Gil. Songs: "The Farmer's Song", "Milk the Cow" Shop: Animal Caller Lunch Joke: Cheese and tractors Storybook: "The Farmer and the Farmhand" Field Trip: The farm.

episodes.name: Super Shrimptennial Celebration!
episodes.overview: The kids head to a huge bash their town is hosting at the top of Big Bubble Building.

episodes.name: Happy Clam Day!
episodes.overview: The kids learn about mail before sending out an invitation to a party for Clam.

episodes.name: Can You Dig It?
episodes.overview: The kids go to a dinosaur dig site, where they ask questions about the prehistoric creatures.

episodes.name: Bubble Bites!
episodes.overview: The kids go food shopping in a supermarket.

episodes.name: Haunted House Party!
episodes.overview: The Bubble Guppies are invited to a costume party at a haunted house.

episodes.name: X Marks the Spot!
episodes.overview: The Guppies help a friendly pirate search for treasure using a map.

episodes.name: Happy Holidays, Mr. Grumpfish!
episodes.overview: The Guppies try to spread the joy of the holiday season to Mr. Grumpfish.

episodes.name: The Lonely Rhino!
episodes.overview: The Guppies learn about the zoo while trying to find a friend for a lonely rhinoceros.

episodes.name: Bubble Puppy's Fin-tastic Fairy Tale!
episodes.overview: Once upon a time, Molly and Gil went up a hill to fetch a pail of water. But when a mean witch, played by Wanda Sykes, turns Bubble Puppy into a frog. Molly and Gil seek the help of Little Red Riding Hood (Oona), Goldilocks (Deema), and Jack (Goby), they soon learn from a magic mirror (Nonny, who was cursed by the Witch's mean green bubble potion by being trapped in the mirror and was forced to work for her), that they can change the potion to one that that will undo her curse is to put Red Riding Hood's cookies, Goldilocks' porridge, and Jack's golden egg into the potion. And with the help of Jack's beans, the Bubble Guppies plan to stop the witch, but can they save the world from being turned into frogs?

episodes.name: The Cowgirl Parade!
episodes.overview: Yee-haw! Molly wants to be a cowgirl like Dusty, the riden'-est, ropin'-est cowgirl in the parade! But when Dusty's calf gets into trouble, Molly has to use everything she's learned to save the day.

episodes.name: Firefighter Gil to the Rescue!
episodes.overview: When Gil and Bubble Puppy get stuck in a tree, a heroic team of firefighters comes to the rescue! But what happens when the firefighters get stuck in a tree? Can Gil and his team of Bubble Guppy firefighters work together and save the day?

episodes.name: A Tooth on the Looth!
episodes.overview: Deema has a loose tooth, and when it falls out, she's going to get a visit from the Tooth Fairy! Until then, the Bubble Guppies have lots to discover about keeping a healthy smile.

episodes.name: Humunga-Truck!
episodes.overview: There are lots of different kinds of trucks, but only one that can turn into a giant robot - Humunga-Truck! The Bubble Guppies learn all about different kinds of trucks on their way to the big Truck Show!

episodes.name: Check It Out!
episodes.overview: Gil and his friends dive into Gil's favorite books to find his missing library card.

episodes.name: The Beach Ball!
episodes.overview: Molly's friend needs the Guppies' help to finish her work in time to attend the Big Beach Ball.

episodes.name: The Sizzling Scampinis!
episodes.overview: The Guppies perform in a circus.

episodes.name: Construction Psyched!
episodes.overview: Goby must retrace his steps to find his lost toy at a construction site.

episodes.name: Bubble-Cadabra!
episodes.overview: The Guppies stand in a for a magician and attempt to make an elephant disappear.

episodes.name: Bubble Duckies!
episodes.overview: Flying ducks get lost in a storm cloud and must be rescued.

episodes.name: Triple Track Train Race!
episodes.overview: A steam locomotive enters a train race, but a herd of cows on the tracks threatens to derail its chances of winning.

episodes.name: Only the Sphinx Nose!
episodes.overview: Join the Bubble Guppies on an adventure to ancient Egypt, as they follow clues across the desert.

episodes.name: Sir Nonny the Nice!
episodes.overview: Nonny is on a quest to become a real knight! He has a shield. He has a suit of armor.

episodes.name: Good Hair Day!
episodes.overview: Learn all about hair! Gil needs to get his hair cut before picture day.

episodes.name: Get Ready for School!
episodes.overview: Oona's friend is worried about his first day of school; the guppies reveal that school is a great place to learn, play and meet new friends.

episodes.name: The Police Cop-etition!
episodes.overview: Officer Miranda teaches Gil and the other children how police officers use laws to keep people safe.

episodes.name: The Elephant Trunk-a-Dunk!
episodes.overview: Gil and his friends attend a basketball game played by elephants.

episodes.name: The Super Ballet Bowl!
episodes.overview: Molly and the Guppies want to learn how to tell a story through dance.

episodes.name: The Wizard of Oz-tralia!
episodes.overview: After Molly and Gil meet Bobby, a nature show host from Australia, they can't wait to learn all about Australian animals. From marsupials to the amazing platypus, the Guppies can't get enough of the creatures Down Under!

episodes.name: The Arctic Life!
episodes.overview: Gil tries to head to the North Pole after learning about Arctic animals.

episodes.name: Puppy Love!
episodes.overview: Bubble Puppy becomes ill and is treated by a veterinarian while Gil makes him a get-well card.

episodes.name: The Puppy and the Ring! (1)
episodes.overview: In the mythical land of Bubbledom, the evil Night Wizard has taken the magical Ring of the Sun! Someone needs to save the daytime! Will Molly and Gil return the Ring to the Sun King, or will it be nighttime in Bubbledom forever?

episodes.name: The Puppy and the Ring! (2)
episodes.overview: Conclusion. A mythical land is trapped in darkness after the Night Wizard swipes the enchanted Ring of the Sun, so Molly and Gil try to retrieve the ring and restore daylight to the land.

episodes.name: The Amusement Parking Lot!
episodes.overview: The children try to figure out how to get Mr. Grouper's car started after it breaks down on the way to an amusement park.

episodes.name: Good Morning, Mr. Grumpfish!
episodes.overview: The children try to teach Mr. Grumpfish about their favorite things when he is their substitute teacher.

episodes.name: The Oyster Bunny!
episodes.overview: It's time for baby animals! Goby dreams up the Oyster Bunny, a mysterious character who loves baby animals. Can the Guppies follow an egg trail to find the elusive Oyster Bunny? A tasty treat awaits them!

episodes.name: The Unidentified Flying Orchestra!
episodes.overview: After Gil and Molly meet a conductor, the Guppies want to join an orchestra.

episodes.name: Come to Your Senses!
episodes.overview: Oh no! Nonny broke his glasses! When they're fixed, Nonny is determined to retrieve them on his own. But to do it, he'll have to depend on his other four senses to reach the glasses store before it closes!

episodes.name: The Bubble Bee-athalon!
episodes.overview: The kids use teamwork to turn nectar into honey in time for the queen bee's afternoon tea.

episodes.name: Party at Sea!
episodes.overview: The kids celebrate boats with a bash at sea, but the festivities are threatened by snow-cone ice.

episodes.name: Bubble Scrubbies!
episodes.overview: The Guppies perform a "soap opera" to teach Mr. Grouper about good hygiene.

episodes.name: Swimtastic Check-Up!
episodes.overview: The Mayor gets a tummy ache while training for Bubbletucky's annual marathon and has to go to the hospital to get checked out.

episodes.name: Gobble Gobble Guppies!
episodes.overview: When Molly and Gil discover the pumpkin patch is empty, their turkey friend leads them on a hunt to find the guilty party.

episodes.name: A Very Guppy Christmas!
episodes.overview: When Mr. Grouper's van gets stuck in the holiday snow, Mr. Claws and his horse, Snowflake, come to the rescue.

episodes.name: Puddleball!
episodes.overview: When rain spoils a game of kickball, Gil invents a new game; Bubble Puppy must overcome his fear of thunder to save the game.

episodes.name: The Running of the Bullfrogs!
episodes.overview: Gil and Goby bring a tadpole to school to watch him grow into a frog.

episodes.name: Bubble Kitty!
episodes.overview: When Molly and Gil find a lost kitten named Bubble Kitty, they help take the cat home to Meownt Rushmore.

episodes.name: Super Guppies!
episodes.overview: When Molly and Gil bring a comic book to school, all the Guppies want to be superheroes! In the comic book's pages, the smelly villain Sid Fishy aims to make the whole city stinky! Molly and Gil dive into the adventure as Guppy Girl and Bubble Boy, but can our heroes stop Sid?

episodes.name: A Dolphin Is a Guppy's Best Friend!
episodes.overview: Molly, Gil and the Guppies must lead a baby dolphin named Buddy to the surprise birthday party his pod is throwing for him.

episodes.name: The Glitter Games!
episodes.overview: Molly helps a princess-in-training with her manners, and together they become princesses in the hallowed Glitter Games.

episodes.name: Costume Boxing!
episodes.overview: Molly performs in the quick-change dress-up match during Fashion Week in Bubbletucky and ends up on the cover of a fashion magazine.

episodes.name: The New Doghouse!
episodes.overview: When an accident destroys Bubble Puppy's doghouse, the Guppies team up with the entire neighborhood to build Bubble Puppy's dream home.

episodes.name: Fruit Camp!
episodes.overview: Deema must try broccoli if she wants to earn her badge.

episodes.name: Guppy Movers!
episodes.overview: The gang help Skip move after his moving-day plans go off track.

episodes.name: Batterball!
episodes.overview: Molly and Gil visit chef Stef's kitchen and witness how bubblecakes are prepared. Later, the kids play batterball.

episodes.name: The Temple of the Lost Puppy!
episodes.overview: Bubble Puppy disappears after he bites down on ancient magic bone, so the Guppies must embark on an epic booby-trapped adventure to find their lost puppy!

episodes.name: Space Guppies!
episodes.overview: When the evil robot Major Bummer tries to eliminate music from the galaxy, Princess Molly and the Guppies must restore peace, harmony and melody.

episodes.name: The New Year's Dragon!
episodes.overview: The Guppies are excited for China's Lunar New Year Festival, where they will operate a giant festival dragon the grand parade.

episodes.name: Sheep Doggy!
episodes.overview: Farmer Joe's baby lamb wanders off during a storm, Bubble Puppy becomes a sheepdog to save the day.

episodes.name: Bubble Baby!
episodes.overview: Molly is going to have a new sibling, the Guppies get excited about babies. Everyone goes to meet the new baby.

episodes.name: Guppy Style! (1)
episodes.overview: The Guppies hit the road to see a concert by Stylee, a singing sensation known for her fabulous styles; Molly becomes a pop star to step on stage with Stylee.

episodes.name: Guppy Style! (2)
episodes.overview: The Guppies hit the road to see a concert by Stylee, a singing sensation known for her fabulous styles; Molly becomes a pop star to step on stage with Stylee.

episodes.name: The Summer Camp Games!
episodes.overview: Summer is here! Molly, Gil, and the rest of the Guppies celebrate the season with lots of outdoor fun. Gil uses his summer camping skills to rescue Bubble Puppy during the Summer Camp Games!

episodes.name: Trick-or-Treat, Mr. Grumpfish!
episodes.overview: Happy Halloween! Molly, Gil, and the rest of the Guppies are picking out costumes, trick-or-treating, and turning their classroom into a haunted house! It'll have to be really spooky if they want to scare Mr. Grumpfish!

episodes.name: The New Guppy!
episodes.overview: The Sea Witch steals the Guppies' magical jewels, so she can rule the Seven Seas! Will the Guppies get their jewels back, and stop her before it's too late?

episodes.name: Secret Agent Nonny!
episodes.overview: It's Secret Agent Nonny's birthday, and he's on a mission to deliver mysterious messages to all of his agent friends. Turns out, they're invitations to his own surprise birthday party!

episodes.name: Kingdom of Clean!
episodes.overview: Deema the evil ruler wants a medieval kingdom to stay dirty, with a giant ogre as her assistant. The rest of the guppies must stop them and get the kingdom clean again.

episodes.name: The Good, the Sad, and the Grumpy!
episodes.overview: When Mr. Grumpfish turns up in Happy Junction, he makes everyone in town really grumpy, including Sheriff Molly, who must find a way to help everyone handle their tricky emotions.

episodes.name: Ocean Patrol
episodes.overview: The Guppies must stop Windy Pete and first mate Oona when they sail around the world and blast tropical climates with snow.

episodes.name: Rockin' Out
episodes.overview: Goby and Gil go on a quest to get a geode at the top of a volcano. They try to make it back to the Rocky Valley Rock Show in time to enter the contest for best rock.

episodes.name: Genie In A Bubble!
episodes.overview: When Nonny, Gil and Zooli conjure a genie, she agrees to grant whoever brings her the most precious gift a wish.

episodes.name: A Furry Tale
episodes.overview: Hansel and Gretel have to get Bubble Puppy and Bubble Kitty home safe to the Furry Godmother, but they're being stalked by a witch.

episodes.name: Super Baby!
episodes.overview: When super villain Lady Goo Goo starts changing everyone into babies, it's up to Guppy Girl and Bubble Boy to stop her before they get turned into babies too!

episodes.name: Dragons N' Roses!
episodes.overview: When Agnes the Dragon moves to the Kingdom of Roses, everyone is afraid of her fearsome roar except for Zooli, who befriends Agnes and shows her friends how lovable Agnes really is.

episodes.name: Ninja Season!
episodes.overview: Gil wants to be a ninja, but his ninja teacher just keeps giving him random tasks to do; frustrated, Gil is about to give up when another ninja challenges him, and he realizes he's been learning ninja skills all along.

episodes.name: Snow Squad to the Rescue!
episodes.overview: Gil is convinced a yeti is to blame when sleeping bags go missing.

episodes.name: Too Bright for Movie Night!
episodes.overview: If the Moon People can find a way to make it dark during the day, the Sun People agree to turn off their giant night light so the Moon People can enjoy their movie night.

episodes.name: The Guppies Save Christmas!
episodes.overview: On Christmas Eve, Molly, Gil, and Bubble Puppy discover Santa's lost list in the snow. To return the list safely to the North Pole, they have to keep it out of the hands of the Christmas-hating Humbug.

episodes.name: The Mighty, Untidy Titans!
episodes.overview: When some untidy Titans (played by Guppies) start messing up Zooli, Nonny and Oona's goat farm, the goat herders must journey to the Titans' cloud realm to ask them to tidy up.

episodes.name: Alison in Wonderland!
episodes.overview: Mail carrier molly is trying to deliver a Friendship Day card for someone named Alison in a place called Wonderland.

episodes.name: It's a Lizard!
episodes.overview: When showman Gil's real live dragon (actually a Komodo dragon) gets loose in the small town of Bubbleville, it's up to Pet Finders Oona and Zooli to track the lizard down and return it to its home on Komodo Island.

episodes.name: Swinging in the Rainforest!
episodes.overview: City-slicker umbrella sellers Molly and Gil set up shop in the Amazon rainforest.

episodes.name: Werewolves of Bubbledon!
episodes.overview: On Halloween eve in the foggy town of Bubbledon, everyone is nervous because there's a werewolf on the loose; monster detectives Molly, Gil, and Dr. Pupson are on the case and try to find the critter before Halloween is canceled.

episodes.name: Fogzilla!
episodes.overview: It's lighthouse keeper Deema's birthday, but when a monster named Fogzilla keeps blowing out her lighthouse, she needs to figure out how to get Capt. Molly's ship, carrying her birthday cake to shore, or there won't be a party.

episodes.name: Bigfoot Crossing!
episodes.overview: On the hottest day of the year, Rangers Goby and Gil's job is to make sure pedestrians reach the lake safely; however, Bigfoot causes issues when he removes the stop signs from the park.

episodes.name: A Load of Litterbugs!
episodes.overview: On the U.S.S. Recycler, Captain Deema and her crew strive to leave every planet cleaner than they found it. However, their mission is put to the test when a crew of messy Litterbugs, led by the evil Garbage Khan, take over their ship.

episodes.name: A Giant Harvest Day!
episodes.overview: Holiday Cooks Molly and Gil, on a mission to save the town's Harvest Day (Thanksgiving) feast, must retrieve a Golden Tomato from magical Tall Tale Farms; but first, their food knowledge is tested by three guardians.

episodes.name: Christmas Is Coming!
episodes.overview: On a quest to attend King Grouper's Christmas party and deliver a promised tree, Lady Oona and Lord Goby must face the ravages of winter and a mysterious Freezy Dragon, who seems intent on keeping them from the festivities.

episodes.name: The Holiday Pirates!
episodes.overview: In Holiday Land, there's a town for every holiday until Pirate Myra uses Wizard Grouper's magic wand to turn every town into Pirate Town; it's up to Molly and Gil to restore Holiday Land back to normal.

episodes.name: Bubble Puppysaurus!
episodes.overview: When small-town "puppy-saurus" Bubble Puppy gets picked to go against the reigning champ Boom Boom T-Rex in the Tough Roarier competition, it's a battle of strength, speed and, above all, heart.

episodes.name: Winter Sports Chompetition!
episodes.overview: Gil and Bubble Puppy are competing in the Winter Sports Chompetition, a competition for athletes and their dogs; they hope to stop reigning champs Coldsnap and his dog Mr. Husky from cheating to win the gold.

episodes.name: The SS Friendship!
episodes.overview: Capt. Deemo and first mate Gil pilot their steampunk sub to different ocean habitats so they can deliver Friendship Day bubblegrams to all their friends; along the way, they find themselves being chased by a kraken.

episodes.name: Something Fishy Going On!
episodes.overview: Police Officers Molly and Gil are tracking some mysterious lights that have been popping up around town; with the help of several nocturnal animal friends, they discover the lights aren't aliens but anglerfish.

episodes.name: Robo Puppy!
episodes.overview: Robot Mechanic Molly and Robo Puppy must stop a bossy cyborg named the Glitch when it hacks all of the robots in Robotopolis and forces them to dance "The Robot."

episodes.name: Race to the Oasis!
episodes.overview: Ice cream sellers Molly and Gil are trying to deliver ice cream to a waterpark on the other side of a hot desert. Will they get the ice cream across the desert, unmelted, before the Rattlers catch them?

episodes.name: Escape from Volcano Island!
episodes.overview: Skipper Molly and First Mate Gil are shipwrecked on Volcano Island, and it's about to erupt. When parts of their boat start to mysteriously disappear, will they be able to make it off the island in time?

episodes.name: Mountain Ninja Rescue!
episodes.overview: Ninjas Zooli and Oona are excited for their first mission: escorting snow monkey Moshi up Mt. Danger to join his troop. But it won't be easy: a storm looms, and mischievous Moshi is causing trouble. Will they complete their mission?

episodes.name: The Jaw-some Sharkventure!
episodes.overview: Zooli and her crew of Marine Biologists escort their new friends Baby Shark and his pilot fish William to visit Baby Shark's great-great-great-great-great Uncle Slow Mo, and help them escape the determined fisherman who's chasing them.

episodes.name: Taste Buddies!
episodes.overview: When chefs Molly and Gil bring their tasty food truck to Bland Land, they discover that Baron von Bland only lets his subjects eat Bland Bread. Yuck!

episodes.name: The Kingdom of Sleepwell!
episodes.overview: All is not well in the normally well-rested Kingdom of Sleepwell. Princess Deema can't fall asleep. Her Royal Court comes to her aid, but when even magic doesn't work, she learns that all she needed to do was follow her bedtime routine.

episodes.name: A Big Splash!
episodes.overview: On the Shimmy-Shimmy Islands, everyone's preparing for Queen Zooli's Dance Party. But each time they practice their songs, they're splashed by a huge wave. Will they figure out who's causing the waves before the party is canceled?

episodes.name: Bubble Medics to the Rescue!
episodes.overview: In Ancient Greece, Paramedics Zooli and Gil get a call for help from Nonny, so they race to him in their flying chariot ambulance. Along the way, they're pursued by a giant Cyclops. Will they reach Nonny before the Cyclops catches them?

episodes.name: Search for the Great Gorilla!
episodes.overview: When Primatologists Zooli and Gil search the rain forest for a Silverback Gorilla, they're chased into an ancient temple by a robotic Silverback - who turns out to just be a tiny marmoset guarding a sanctuary of mountain gorillas.

episodes.name: Don't Yuck My Yum!
episodes.overview: In the Gourmet Galaxy, everyone loves yummy food. But when General Yuck turns everything icky, only a recipe for delicious Moon Muffins can stop her. Master Chef Goby and his apprentice Deema must bake those muffins and save the galaxy.

episodes.name: Mystery on the Guppy Express!
episodes.overview: When Oona's Bubble Kitty goes missing aboard the Guppy Express, sly Detective Nonny steps in to help. Knowing the cat must still be on board, they race to find her before the train reaches its next stop--and the kitty may be lost for good.

episodes.name: Puppy Girl and Super Pup!
episodes.overview: When super villain Felina Meow starts turning all the dogs at the annual Dog Show into cats, it's up to superheroes Puppy Girl and Super Pup to stop her. Will they foil her cat-astrophic plan before she turns everyone's pups into kitties?

episodes.name: The Fastest Feather in the Race!
episodes.overview: In the Fastest Feather Race, it's Team Flightless versus cocky Amelia the Peregrine Falcon. Though Penguin Nonny, Ostrich Oona, and Kiwi Goby can't fly, these birds of a feather flock together. Will teamwork be enough to win the trophy?

episodes.name: The Solar Light Spectacular!
episodes.overview: When giant robot Buster steals all the batteries that power Solar City, which runs on the sun's energy, it's up to Solar Power Workers Nonny and Goby to stop him and get the lights back on before the big light show is canceled.

episodes.name: The Kingdom of Laughs-a-Lot!
episodes.overview: Jesters Goby and Gil arrive in the Kingdom of NeverLaugh, where King Grumpfish declares that he'll outlaw laughter forever if no one can make him laugh before sundown. Will the Jesters be able to crack him up before it's too late?

episodes.name: The Big Rig Bandit!
episodes.overview: When reckless hyena Spotty steals young elephant Eli from the savanna, Wildlife Rangers Zooli and Goby hop into their big rig to rescue him. But when the big rig chase lands Spotty and Eli in danger, it's up to the Guppies to save the day.

episodes.name: The Ultra Spy Tool!
episodes.overview: When supervillain Dr. Coldfinger takes Curly Q's newest invention, the Ultra Spy Tool, Secret Agents Molly, Goby and Spy Pup must travel across the world to find and infiltrate his North Pole lair.

episodes.name: Zooli's New Pet
episodes.overview: The Guppies excitedly wonder what kind of animal Zooli is adopting for a pet. They know she likes almost all furry, feathery, and scaly creatures, so guessing what she'll pick can be difficult.

episodes.name: Trouble in Harmony Valley!
episodes.overview: Everyone in the Old West town of Harmony Valley loves playing music together. When noisy Billy Joe Strumlouder rides into town to sabotage their tunes, Sheriff Zooli must save the day.

episodes.name: The Three Guppeteers!
episodes.overview: When a Gargoyle steals all the gifts and decorations for Countess Zooli's surprise birthday party, the French villagers call in the Three Guppeteers (played by Molly, Deema and Oona) to save the day.

episodes.name: A Slow Day in Zippy City!
episodes.overview: Everything is fast in Zippy City, from the trolley to the mail. But Tiny the Slug and the Opposite Crew slow everything down to the opposite.

episodes.name: See You Later, Alligator!
episodes.overview: Bayou Chicken Farmers Deema and Goby discover an unusual egg on their farm one morning, and set off on a bayou river adventure to find the egg's mama.
